{
  "metadata": {
    "description": "Laptop GPU / SoC hardware data for LLM hardware calculator. Covers discrete mobile GPUs (NVIDIA RTX 40/50 series, AMD RDNA3 mobile), Apple Silicon SoCs (M3/M4 families), Intel Arc integrated GPUs, and Raspberry Pi SBCs.",
    "data_version": "1.0.0",
    "last_updated": "2025-03",
    "coverage_notes": "Focuses on 2023–2025 released hardware. TGP ranges reflect manufacturer-allowed min/max across OEM implementations. TFLOPS marked with ~ are computed estimates from known CUDA counts and boost clocks. Apple Silicon TFLOPS are GPU-only (compute shader path); the Neural Engine provides additional INT8/BF16 throughput not captured here. Unified memory is shared CPU+GPU on Apple Silicon and Qualcomm — the full pool is accessible to the GPU/NPU.",
    "llm_relevance_notes": "For LLM inference, vram_gb and vram_bandwidth_gbps are the two most critical fields. Memory bandwidth determines decode token/sec. VRAM capacity determines max model size at a given quantization. Apple Silicon chips are uniquely valuable because unified_memory_max_gb is the effective VRAM ceiling — far exceeding any discrete laptop GPU."
  },
